name: Upper Major Creek
description:
Introduction

A significant tributary of the Columbia River, Major Creek has one notable waterfall in its upper western fork. This is likely not a terrific destination on its own, but more of an objective for Portland-area obsessives.

Approach

Descent

  • Some short slides.
  • Major Creek Falls.

About 0.3mi further downstream (just south of the powerlines) are two more drops:

  • 35ft.
  • 25ft.

Exit

Red tape

Use a map & GPS to avoid private property and respect all postings.

  • Property boundaries from Klickitat County Parcel Map.
